Text.Value: Do I look like a bloody tour guide?
Not since the bloody eagles turned up and turfed me out of my first nest.
Curses! I was going to ask you to do the same thing, of course that tit got there first!
Stealing is the art of taking. It's a beautiful thing.
Too bad. Time to die.
I'm not just hungry! But, also, yes. I am hungry.
Thieves? What did they steal?
Glorious! Feathers bloody everywhere, mate! Feels good to be home in my nest.
That's great - where's my reward?
Is that why you're grumpy then? You're hungry?
So the eagles are pricks for stealing a nest, but you're not?
So am I, and you look like a perfect portion.
Leave.
I'm not here to take. Have you seen any of my people nearby?
Well, it feels rubbish. I miss my roof-nest.
*Chirp! Chirp!*
I can fight the eagles and get your nest back.
I'll either be killed or ask another poor sap to fight them again.
Attack .
Oh, sure, a nest. But it's not my nest. That's up on the roof, with the eagles. Eagles are pricks.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Pending on camera cut, may just need a standard Idle like BIRD_BlueJay_Rig_CINE_Idle_01 <OllieS>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player sees a shot of the roof in the distance.
EditorData.NodeContext: "my nest" said with a deep longing

Text.Value: Why the roof?
Exactly right. Not all humans can grasp bird ethics, you should be proud.
That's a lot of attitude from a little bird.
That's exactly how it works, and it's my turn. Get out, or I'll turn you into stew.
Thank you. I'll keep an eye on the roof. Rude bastards, those eagles. Deserve a little comeuppance.
It's a good lookout spot for food...
I'm expecting a powerful artefact.
Hah! You? Kill an eagle? But if you think you can...

EditorData.NodeContext: Incredulous, eagles are the scariest things ever for them

Text.Value: You're in luck, the eagles are dead.
Actually, my kind do birth eggs.
I wish there was something I could give you in return. Oh! Tell you what...
Surely the eagles need a nest as much as you?
They're not invincible, I just haven't gotten round to it yet.
Not again! No! Abandon nest!
Leave.
Bet these eagle corpses'll scare any more of the big-wing bastards away.
Hah! The eagles couldn't finish me off, and they're much bigger than you.
Do you want me to go and deal with the eagles for you?
Wait, so if that's not your nest, whose is it?
I finished off those eagles for you, the top of the monastery is all yours.
Leave.
Leave.
Maybe I wouldn't be so little if I had a proper dinner and a nest.
It's about to get less fair. You have to leave this nest now, or else.
Let me guess. Defeat. It's to be expected, eagles are invincible after all.
Weird. Does your kind like mysterious buried treasure more than bullying birds?
Eagles can be killed? Incredible! Thank you, kind, tall, ugly stranger. My nest awaits.
*Alcoholic lizards didn't show up much in your studies of the natural world.*
Hah, not likely! That bird is long gone, no way you talked to them.
I can't help but notice you have a nest right there.
Typical arrogance. Remember, tall one, pride comes before the fall. A very long fall.
You're not the first to be scared of the eagles, there's no shame in admitting it.
Leave.
I'm sorry... I'm just a bird. I don't have things to give you. Although...
Leave.
Leave.
I'm not here to take. I'm looking for a githyanki crche. Have you seen one?
I'll see what I can do.
It's not even like the eagles need my nest, the drunk lizards they eat aren't hard to catch.
Why do you want it? You lot don't even lay eggs! Let me have it - I'll make it worth your while.
Some poor little tit who wasn't paying attention.
I suppose I could turn you into dinner.
Steal? Eagles are bigger, they just take... Nest, prey, everything. That's how it works here.
Leave.
Did someone steal something from you?
Glad I could help.
I've already killed the eagles, luckily for you.
No! Not again! I'd only just finished making nest number two!
It's not bloody fair! I got there first! The eagles don't even need it!
When I escaped the eagles, I spotted something buried near that ferry dock. Might be worth a look.
I don't have time for petty bird squabbles.
Fine. What do you have for me?
I'm not here to take - just exploring. Seen anything interesting?
I've got nothing left to take, so you might as well shove off!
What will you do if more eagles return to the roof?
Is there not enough food around here?
That doesn't sound very fair.
Don't you have anything better to do than bother me?
*While quite vague, 'drunk lizards' could well point to kobolds, who tend to operate in packs.*
I'm here to avenge the bird you kicked out. Time to shove off.
*Chirp!*
Is that it? No reward for my heroic deed?
...then please, please kill the eagles. They're the worst.
No. I'm not running your errands for you.
Try and figure out what these lizards might be.
Attack the whiny bird.
Not on top of the monastery, they don't!
Leave.
Leave.
Who said it's your nest? I killed the eagles. It's mine.
All I know is the roof's the best nest-spot on the whole Chionthar. I got there first, too. Before the thieves showed up.
Leave.

Synopsis: While approaching the gith creche, climbing on a mountain, The player talks to a bird sitting in its nest. It's been bullied by the eagles on the roof, and if scared away it has a nest full of baked goods.
